				\begin{document}$$\sigma ^{\prime}$$\end{document} drastically increases with decreasing T, resulting in a maximum value of ca. 78 for 50 nm thickness (T1). These results suggest that the absorption cross-section of dye molecules depends on the LDOS-enhancement due to the enhanced electric field generated by the PCS (Fig. 3e, peak A). The absorption cross-sections of the dye molecules were expected to decrease with increasing distance from the bottom of the PCS holes because the enhanced electric field decayed exponentially from the bottom of the holes to the free space above the PCS surface. To confirm the contribution of LDOS enhancement to the increase in the absorption sensitivity of the CM, the theoretical responsivity ΔRmodelCa\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
